{"lemma":"سُدَى","slug":"سُدَى","root":"س.د.#","root_slug":"س-د-_","root_link":"/words/roots/س-د-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"سُدَى","root":"سدي","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":0},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n19395","n19397"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8F%D8%AF%D9%8E%D9%89"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n19395","headword_ar":"سَدًى","root":"sdw and sdY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"of a garment, or piece of cloth, (S, M, K, &c.,) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"warp;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA, KL;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"luHomapN","text_ar":"لُحْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M, Msb;) i. e. (Msb [in the M “ and it is said to mean ”]) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"threads"},{"kind":"text","text":"] thereof"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extended longitudinally"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, * Msb, K *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the weaving:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) and it is said to mean the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lower,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lowest, part"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof: (M: [but this is a strange explanation, which I do not find elsewhere:]) it is [said to be] from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~adowu","text_ar":"السَّدْوُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sadaA","text_ar":"سَدَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"] signifying “ the stretching forth the arm, or hand, or the fore leg, towards a thing: ” (Har p. 241: [but it is mentioned in the M as belonging to art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sdY","text_ar":"سدى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and its dual, mentioned below, requires its being so:]) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asodiY~N","text_ar":"اَسْدِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) also [and more commonly] written ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^usodiY~N","text_ar":"اُسْدِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) signifies the same; (M, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sadaApN","text_ar":"سَدَاةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) or this last is the n. un. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sadFY","text_ar":"سَدًى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, TA,) having a more special signification, (Msb, TA,) [as though meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a warp,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sort of warp;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"luHomapN","text_ar":"لُحْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be affixed for the purpose of assimilating the word to its contr."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sadFY","text_ar":"سَدًى"},{"kind":"text","text":", with which it is often coupled:] the dual [of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sadFY","text_ar":"سَدًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sadayaAni","text_ar":"سَدَيَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb, TA:) and the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asodiyapN","text_ar":"اَسْدِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(accord. to the S) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asodaA='N","text_ar":"اَسْدَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^anota biluHomapK walaA sadaApK","text_ar":"مَا اَنْتَ بِلُحْمَةٍ وَلَا سَدَاةٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou art neither a woof nor a warp"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is said to him who neither harms nor profits. (TA. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"satFY","text_ar":"سَتًى"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b2-  Hence, as being likened thereto, (M, [see 2, second sentence,]) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Honey in its comb;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uhodN","text_ar":"شُهْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ahodN","text_ar":"شَهْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, K, TA.) ―         -b3-  And (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A benefit, benefaction, favour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K, TA. [See also the next two sentences.]) ―         -b4-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nightdew;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K;) by means of which seedproduce lives: (S, * Msb:) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sadFY","text_ar":"سَدًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nadFY","text_ar":"نَدًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"are syn. [and both applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dew in an absolute sense"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asodaA='N","text_ar":"اَسْدَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.) ―         -b5-  And (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Liberality, bounty, munificence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"generosity;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as being likened thereto; and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nadFY","text_ar":"نَدًى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ndw","text_ar":"ندو"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ndY","text_ar":"ندى"},{"kind":"text","text":".) [See an ex. in a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riqobapN","text_ar":"رِقْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Green dates,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with their"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$amaAriyx","text_ar":"شَمَارِيخ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fruit-stalks"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (M;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sadaA='N","text_ar":"سَدَا=ءٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;) of the dial of El-Yemen: n. un. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sadaApN","text_ar":"سَدَاةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sadaA='apN","text_ar":"سَدَا=ءَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, TA,) on the authority of AA, and of Sh also, who says that they are of the dial. of El-Medeeneh. (TA.) [See also the last sentence of the next paragraph: and see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sayaAbN","text_ar":"سَيَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]       -A3-  Also sometimes used in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sudFY","text_ar":"سُدًى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K.) See this latter word."}],"source_refs":["Msb","M","K","TA","S"]},{"entry_id":"n19397","headword_ar":"سُدًى","root":"sdw and sdY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sadFY","text_ar":"سَدًى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) the former the more common, (S, K,) used alike as sing. and pl., (S, * M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Left, let alone,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"neglected;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"left to pasture by itself"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by themselves;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K;) applied to a camel, (K, TA,) and to camels: (S, K, TA:) you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAqapN sudFY","text_ar":"نَاقَةٌ سُدًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ibilN sudFY","text_ar":"اـِبِلٌ سُدًى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAdK","text_ar":"سَادٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same [as a sing. epithet]. (M, K.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ayaHosabu A@loA_inosaAnu A^ano yutoraka sudFY","text_ar":"اَيَحْسَبُ ا@لْاـِنْسَانُ اَنْ يُتْرَكَ سُدًى"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [lxxv. 36], means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Doth man think that he is to be left to himself, uncontrolled, neither commanded nor forbidden?"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}